### Test Orders API

### 1. Get all products
GET https://localhost:5001/api/orders/products
Accept: application/json

### 2. Place an order
POST https://localhost:5001/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "deliveryAddress": {
    "street": "Str. Mihai Viteazu 123",
    "city": "Cluj-Napoca",
    "postalCode": "400394",
    "country": "Romania"
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "{{productId1}}",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 2500
    },
    {
      "productId": "{{productId2}}",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 100
    }
  ]
}

### 3. Generate Invoice
POST https://localhost:5001/api/invoices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "totalAmount": 2700,
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "paymentMethod": "CreditCard"
}

### 4. Pickup Package
POST https://localhost:5001/api/packages/pickup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "{{orderId}}",
  "awb": null,
  "pickupDate": "2025-11-08T10:00:00",
  "deliveryAddress": {
    "street": "Str. Mihai Viteazu 123",
    "city": "Cluj-Napoca",
    "postalCode": "400394",
    "country": "Romania"
  },
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "simulateDelivery": true
}

